IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Crime: Theft -$100 x41 / Theft Scheme Location: 15300 McMullen Hwy Cumberland MD / Weis Markets / Business Scene Processing: Loss Prevention Officer was able to provide surveillance video, spreadsheets of each individual theft. Narrative: On 11/07/2023 at approximately 1404 hrs, I was dispatched by the Cumberland Barrack to respond to 15300 McMullen Hwy, Cumberland, Weis Markets, for a report of a theft. The barrack advised this theft occurred prior, that the suspect was not currently at the store, however they know who the suspect is. Upon my arrival I contacted Ms Tara Jacobs, W/F, DOB 04/28/1998. Ms Jacobs holds the position of Loss Prevention Officer at Weis. Tara advised she works at several Weis locations, however this crime all occurred at store #291, Cresaptown. Tara advised on 10/10/2023 she came across an instance in the suspicious activity binder where associates noticed that a female subject failed to scan merchandise in her cart before leaving with the merchandise. After the woman left, they pulled the receipt and confirmed that the items were not on her receipt. She then pulled the transaction and compared it to CCTV footage, She advised on the footage she observed the woman scanned some merchandise in her cart but left some cat foods in her cart. She said she also grabbed a handful of merchandise from her cart and just placed it into bags, never attempting to scan them. She then finished her transaction and left the store with the items she failed to scan. Tara advised she then pulled the club card linked to the transaction (40205705518) which came back to Dotti Morgan. Tara advised she ran Morgans transaction history and was able to find 41 transactions over a time frame from 07/10/2023 to 11/05/2023 where she failed to scan merchandise each time. Tara advised commonly she would grab multiple bags of cat food and leave them in her cart and not even attempt to scan them. Other times she would grab a handful of items and throw them into a bag. She advised there would also be days she would double items up, only scanning one, but taking multiples. Tara advised on 11/07/2023 she returned to store 291, Cresaptown and continued watching CCTV footage of Morgans transactions. She then began to identify items and place them onto a spreadsheet. She advised she then burned video of the events for the case file. Tara advised all transactions took place via self-checkout. Tara provided a spreadsheet of all 41 thefts, to include what was taken as well as value for each item. 1) 07/10/2023 - Tyson Chicken, Deli Chicken, Old Bay Shrimp for total of $23.99 2) 07/14/2023 - Frisky Cat food, beef tips for total of $20.32 40) 11/02/2023 - DiGiorno pizza, Deli fired chicken for total of $25.67 41) 11/05/2023 - Deli Chicken for total of $5.00 All above thefts occurred between the listed dates ( 07/10/2023 to 11/05/2023 ) at store #291 Cresaptown Weis Market. The total loss for Weis over that time frame is $1,031.59. All above thefts were done by the same woman identified as Dotti Morgan. I then was able to run a browse on Dotti Morgan and obtained her information to include her picture. Tara was able to look at the picture and did positively identify her as the suspect, Dotti Jane Morgan, W/F, DOB 03/17/1959 with an address of 14220 Elton Dr SW Cumberland MD. Tara was then provided with the case number for her records. After the above I responded to 14220 Elton Dr in an attempt to locate Dotti Morgan. When I arrived at the address Dotti met me in the front yard of the residence. At that time I was able to speak with Dotti in regard to the reported thefts. Dotti advised she was not denying the theft, however she was not doing it on purpose, and she was not aware she was even doing it. I asked Dotti if she was having trouble affording food, and she advised she was not. She stated she has trouble hearing and can not hear the beep when you scan items and thinks maybe that is what was happening. She said she scans or at least attempts to scan all her items, that she uses the self-checkout because there are no aisles open with a live person. Dotti also advised she does have mental blocks from time to time and doesnt realize what she is doing. Dotti at that time did offer to go pay for the items, however I advised her due to the fact it happened over periods of 4 months and 41 separate times that was not an option at this point. I advised Dotti I would be applying for charges, and she would have to come to court, and she agreed. After the above I contacted the complainant Tara Jabobs again. I asked Tara during all above thefts if Ms Morgan was attempting to scan the property at all, that she said she has trouble hearing the beeps. Tara advised Ms Morgan does not make any attempt to scan the stolen items that sometimes she just leaves them in her cart and places scanned items on top of them and other times she just takes them from her cart and places them directly in bags, never attempting to scan them at all. Due to the above facts, I am in the process of requesting charges against Ms. Dotti Jane Morgan, W/F, DOB 03/17/1959 for 41 counts of theft under $100 and count of theft scheme. Case open.
